        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 18 at 2:23PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 223 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Glenwood Springs, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glenwood Springs and Shoshone.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 114 and 133.
Colorado 82 between mile markers 1 and 5.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
